    "content": "nullIdentify Your Users and Manage Access\nTABLE OF CONTENTS\nClose\nClose\nSearch\nSearch\n Identify Your Users and Manage Access\n Who Is Salesforce Identity For?\n Salesforce Identity Licenses\n Multi-Factor Authentication\n Single Sign-On\n Identity Connect\n Install Identity Connect\n Install Security Update for Identity Connect 3.0.1.2\n Upgrade from Identity Connect 2.1 to Identity Connect 7.1.6\n Upgrade from Identity Connect 3.0.X to Identity Connect 7.1.6\n Upgrade from Identity Connect 7.1.X to Identity Connect 7.1.6\n Custom Login Flows\n Login Access\n Manage User Passwords\n Lightning Login for Password-Free Logins\n Certificate-Based Authentication\n Connected Apps\n External Client Apps\n Authorize Apps with OAuth\n App Launcher\n Manage API Access\n Manage Salesforce User Identities with SCIM\n Salesforce Customer Identity\n Monitor Access to Your Salesforce Orgs and Experience Cloud Sites\n\nYou are here:\n\nSALESFORCE HELP\nDOCS\nIDENTIFY YOUR USERS AND MANAGE ACCESS\nInstall Security Update for Identity Connect 3.0.1.2\n\nIf you’re using Identity Connect 3.0.1.2, install the update to fix a security issue.\n\nREQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS\nAvailable in: both Salesforce Classic (not available in all orgs) and Lightning Experience\nAvailable for an additional cost in: Enterprise, Performance, and Unlimited Editions. Developer Edition includes 10 Identity Connect permission set licenses.\n\n\nUSER PERMISSIONS NEEDED\nTo install Identity Connect:\tManage Users\nTo integrate AD user accounts with Salesforce user accounts:\tIdentity Connect 3 Integration\n\nTo install the Identity Connect 3.0.1.2 update, you must have Identity Connect 3.0.1.2 installed. This update isn’t compatible with any other version of Identity Connect.\n\nNOTE As of the Summer ‘23 release, you can upgrade to Identity Connect 7.1.5, but you can no longer download Identity Connect 2.1 or Identity Connect 3.0.X.X. We recommend that you upgrade to Identity Connect 7.1.5 as soon as possible, because it contains several security enhancements and bug fixes.\nIf Identity Connect 3.0.1.2 is running, stop the service.\nDownload and extract the Identity Connect 3.0.1.2-patch zip file.\nRemove these .jar files from the salesforceIdConnect/bundle directory of your Identity Connect 3.0.1.2 installation.\nidentity-connect-saml-assertion-gen-IC3.0.1.2.jar\nopenidm-external-email-IC3.0.1.2.jar\nopenidm-external-rest-IC3.0.1.2.jar\nCopy the corresponding .jar files from the patch to the salesforceIdConnect/bundle directory of your Identity Connect 3.0.1.2 installation.\n./bundle/identity-connect-saml-assertion-gen-IC3.0.1.2-PATCH.jar\n./bundle/openidm-external-email-IC3.0.1.2-PATCH.jar\n./bundle/openidm-external-rest-IC3.0.1.2-PATCH.jar\nTo delete the Felix cache directory in your Identity Connect 3.0.1.2 installation, use the command rm -rf salesforceIdConnect/felix-cache.\nRestart Identity Connect 3.0.1.2 and test the service to be sure that it’s working as expected.\nDID THIS ARTICLE SOLVE YOUR ISSUE?\nLet us know so we can improve!\nYes\nNo\n ",
